Packages: open source libraray provided by many different developer
URL from you can get packages: npmjs.com

#################################

> JSON: Javascript object notation > way to respresent data
> Key: Value
> Structured and unstructed data
> [

    {
        "name" : "Shweta",
        "city:"Nagpur",
        "Subject": "UI"
    },
    {
        "name" : "Shri",
        "city:"Nagpur",
        "Subject": "UId"
    }

]

###################################
Package.json

> Name,version, description
> Packages in the applications
> Script (Start, Build, Test)
> Entry Point

Steps to generate package.json

> NodeJS must be installed in laptop
> OPen the CMD/Terminal and go inside folder
> npm init
> answer all question
> Type "Yes"

To install any package:

> npm i package name
> npm i > it will go for package.json, look for all the packages and install all related packages

##############################
Global Packages

> Install in dev laptop
> Only to generate app/start app
> will not add in package.json
> Admin access to laptop
> npm i packagename -g

######################
Steps to generate angular app

> one time
> open cmd as admin
> npm i -g @angular/cli

################
Next all time you need new app

> open cmd
> go inside folder
> ng new appname

#### to run the app

> > go into thefolder
> > npm start
> > ng serve
